article.headline: Wright St 88, Kenyon 47
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio (AP) -- DaShaun Wood scored 21 points to lead Wright State to an 88-47 win over Kenyon on Monday night. Wright State (7-6) held Kenyon (3-10) to 33 percent (17-of-52) shooting for the game. Drew Burleson and Everett Spencer each scored 11 for the Raiders, and Jordan Pleiman added 10. Wright State shot 61 percent (34-of-56) and scored 33 points off 17 Kenyon turnovers. Korey Haddox led the Lords with 18 points, the team's only player in double figures.
